---
By: Ralph W. Emerson
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 32
    Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Beauty
---
Never lose an opportunity of seeing anything that is beautiful; for beauty
is God’s handwriting—a wayside sacrament. Welcome it in every fair face, in
every fair sky, in every fair flower, and thank God for it as a cup of
blessing.
